4:
King of Dragons. I, the champion Light, 
request an audience.
8:
What words could an empty husk 
possibly have for me?
12:
Does it not shame thee to skulk before 
magnificence in such a wretched 
state?
15:
It is true that I have fallen. But I do not 
come to talk about myself.
23:
The might of the great King Vagner is 
more valuable than any army. You do 
a great service to Starview—and to 
me.
26:
Stop preening. I do not act for thy 
sake.
29:
I know. It seems you've grown quite 
fond of Stella.
32: The girl? No. I am merely testing her.
34:
I seek one who can break the shackles 
laid upon us for countless years. I seek 
one to rewrite the Law of Ancients.
39:
Is that the spear that goaded you into 
battle?
42:
A sage at the capital told me that the 
Ancients are guides to champions. Yet 
you stood before me as a foe.
43:
I do not understand why one who 
fought so bitterly for life would be so 
quick to choose death over defeat. 
When I spared you, you—
46:
Silence! As thy sage said, we dragons 
are the lapdogs of champions... Kept 
on a leash by an irksome, asinine 
code!
48:
I fought tooth and claw against that 
code, and what for? Mercy? PITY? Dost 
thou fancy thyself a savior? Make no 
mistake. In sparing my life, thou hast 
destroyed ME.
51: ...I fought only to fulfill my duty.
55:
Even now, as a lowly hare, thou darest 
to preach of duty?
57:
Listen well, husk. That duty no longer 
belongs to thee. Thou canst not—and 
WILT not—earn the dragons' support.
59: Even so, I will not abandon my vision.
60:
...Dragon, I do not require your 
allegience. I do not command you to 
fly beneath the banner of champions.
62:
I only ask that you help two young 
people find their path.
66:
Hm... Thou hast put a lot of faith in 
such minute vessels.
68:
I have learned that there is more than 
what meets the eye.
70:
...You have already glimpsed the 
depth of Stella's strength. But there is 
still another with the power to turn the 
tides of fate.
76:
Still another?
Dost thou speak of the boy?!
78:
What power could HE possibly 
possess?
88:
No. You will understand once you 
know him.
I'd also like to hear what you make of 
Alk.
95:
With new form comes new 
perspective.
99:
...Thank you again, Vagner.
Please, keep them safe.
104:
...The flow of destiny has already 
begun to shift.
107:
Very well then. Let us see what new 
shores await mortals and dragons 
alike.
